@node wcsspn
@section @code{wcsspn}---get length of a wide substring 
@strong{Synopsis}
@example
#include <wchar.h>
size_t wcsspn(const wchar_t *@var{s}, const wchar_t *@var{set});

@end example
@strong{Description}@*
The @code{wcsspn} function computes the length of the maximum initial
segment of the wide-character string pointed to by @var{s} which consists
entirely of wide-character codes from the wide-character string
pointed to by @var{set}.

@*
@strong{Returns}@*
The wcsspn() function returns the length @var{s1}; no return value is
reserved to indicate an error.

@*
@strong{Portability}@*
@code{wcsspn} is ISO/IEC 9899/AMD1:1995 (ISO C).

No supporting OS subroutines are required.

@*
